    proc emit_newline from Emitter with emitter

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
`break [label];`. Label is optional - bare break targets the nearest
enclosing loop or switch. ASI hazards apply (no newline between `break`
and label), so we emit a space rather than a line break.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Emit indent + "break"; if label present, emit space + label; semicolon;
newline.
@End Implementation
